																		Want to earn Greenlighting Privileges and/or choose next month&#039;s front-page features?
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404533); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1404533&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610220637" alt="Zyn" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1404533)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1404533); return false;" >Zyn</a></span> <span class="odate time_1609478004 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Jan 2021 05:13</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4859070">
									

<p>Due to the ever-increasing demand for more skilled reviewers to help out in the forums, the Forum Criticism Staff Team has been holding 2-week mentoring sessions to train up-and-coming reviewers. These are called &quot;Flights&quot;.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-243290-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-243290-1')">1</a></sup></p>
<p><strong>What does being part of a Flight mean?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Flight 1 will run from February 1 to February 15. Flight 2 will run from February 15 to February 28.</li>
<li>Mentors (dubbed &quot;commanders&quot;) will work with mentees (&quot;officers&quot;) in the Writing Help forums to critique concepts and drafts while the officers practice and improve their critique skills.</li>
<li>At the start of the Flight, officers will determine their weekly goals for two categories: activity and quality. Activity can be something simple like &quot;crit at least one thread a day&quot;, quality something like &quot;be more familiar with matching authors to helpful resources/guides/example articles&quot;. Commanders will discuss these goals weekly.</li>
<li>Officers will be taught some forum management skills like how to respond (without backseat modding) to a thread that breaks guidelines.</li>
<li>If the officers cannot yet greenlight, they may officially recommend concepts to their commander for greenlight consideration.</li>
<li>Flight teams can have funny/rule of cool names. Commander discretion.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Who are the commanders this month?</strong></p>
<p>The commanders for Flight 1 are <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/karablue9482" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7130109); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=7130109&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609908774" alt="Karablue9482" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=7130109)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/karablue9482" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7130109); return false;">Karablue9482</a></span> and TBA.</p>
<p>The commanders for Flight 2 are <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pedagon" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5903100); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5903100&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609908774" alt="Pedagon" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5903100)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pedagon" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5903100); return false;">Pedagon</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-sage-evergreen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6043564); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6043564&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609908774" alt="Dr Sage Evergreen" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6043564)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-sage-evergreen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6043564); return false;">Dr Sage Evergreen</a></span>, and TBA.</p>
<p><span style="color: blue">Notice: for February, we are opening up commander signups to all individuals who currently have greenlighting privileges! If you're interested in learning about being a commander/mentor, please <a href="http://05command.wikidot.com/butterfly-flights-reference">look at this page for more information</a>.</span></p>
<p><strong>Who can request consideration to be an officer?</strong></p>
<p>Anyone! Newbies and veterans alike are welcome to put their names forth.</p>
<p><strong>What do Flight participants get at the end?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>For as long as the mentorship system continues, <em>Flight teams will select the featured SCP, tale, and GoI format</em> displayed on the front page of the site. Flight team member names will also be displayed on the front page of the site.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-243290-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-243290-2')">2</a></sup></li>
<li><em>Officers deemed ready by their commanders will be given greenlighting privileges</em> (if they do not have them already), and their names and number of successful Flights will be displayed on the <a href="/butterfly-squad-roster">Butterfly Squad Roster</a>.</li>
<li>Flight team member <em>names will be displayed on the corresponding month's Site News page</em>. Officers may optionally provide &quot;flight signoff&quot; messages where they briefly describe the experience and any parting words for future reviewer mentees.</li>
<li>(remember, provision of the rewards is up to commander discretion!)</li>
</ul>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
